You need to add the PostgreSQL JDBC Driver in your project as mentioned in [search.maven.org][1].

**Gradle**:

    implementation &#39;org.postgresql:postgresql:42.2.10&#39;

**Maven**:

```xml
&lt;dependency&gt;
  &lt;groupId&gt;org.postgresql&lt;/groupId&gt;
  &lt;artifactId&gt;postgresql&lt;/artifactId&gt;
  &lt;version&gt;42.2.10&lt;/version&gt;
&lt;/dependency&gt;
```

You can also [download][2] the **JAR** and import to your project manually.

NOTE: Compile as used in this answer is deprecated. Replace with implementation as per [3].


  [1]: https://search.maven.org/artifact/org.postgresql/postgresql
  [2]: https://jdbc.postgresql.org/download.html
  [3]: https://developer.android.com/studio/build/dependencies?utm_source=android-studio#dependency_configurations

