The Unicode character U+1680 is an Ogham space mark, which differs from the standard space character (U+0020) and the other space characters you listed.

In Java&#39;s regular expressions, the `\p{Z}` character class represents any Unicode separator character, which includes all the space characters you listed except for U+1680. Therefore, the regular expression `\p{Zs}|\p{Zl}|\p{Zp}` should match all the space characters you listed except for U+1680.

To precisely match the Ogham space mark (U+1680), you can use the `\p{InOgham}` character class, which matches any character in the Ogham Unicode block. Here&#39;s an example regex pattern that matches all the space characters you listed, including U+1680:

    [\p{Zs}\p{Zl}\p{Zp}\p{InOgham}]

You can use this pattern with a String.replaceAll() method call to remove all occurrences of these space characters from a string:

    String input = &quot;some string with spaces and \u1680 ogham space marks&quot;;
    String output = input.replaceAll(&quot;[\\p{Zs}\\p{Zl}\\p{Zp}\\p{InOgham}]&quot;, &quot;&quot;);
    System.out.println(output); // prints &quot;somestringwithspacesandoghamspacemarks&quot;

